==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|fro|congregacion}}, from {{der|en|la|congregātiō}}, itself from {{m|la|congregō||to herd into a flock}}. Adopted {{c.|1340}} by the English Bible translator {{w|William Tyndale}}, to render the {{cog|grc|ἐκκλησία||those called together, (popular) meeting}} (hence {{cog|la|ecclēsia}}) in his {{w|New Testament}}, and preferred by 16th century Reformers instead of {{l|en|church}}.

